A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Mr. David A. Cook for his service to the Georgia State Senate
2 and the State of Georgia as well as congratulating him upon the grand occasion of his
3 retirement; and for other purposes.
4 WHEREAS, the Office of the Secretary of the Senate was created in 1789 and has proudly
5 served the citizens of the State of Georgia, along with the Georgia State Senate, for over 235
6 years, with the position being most recently filled by the Honorable David A. Cook; and
7 WHEREAS, Mr. Cook is united in love and marriage to Beth Cook and is blessed with two
8 remarkable children and two extraordinary grandchildren; and
9 WHEREAS, in 1976, Mr. Cook approached Secretary of the Senate Hamilton McWhorter
10 Jr. regarding a job in the Senate and was hired as a session assistant, serving as a member of
11 the "crew" and learning the workings of the Secretary's Office from the ground up; and
12 WHEREAS, upon completion of his law degree in 1982, he served as an aide to the Judiciary
13 Committee from 1984 to 1990 under Chairman Nathan Deal; and
