14 WHEREAS, upon then-Senator Deal's election as President Pro Tempore of this body, Mr.
15 Cook was asked to join him as his Chief of Staff, serving from 1990 to 1992, during which
16 time he helped draft the Georgia General Assembly's ethics rules; and
17 WHEREAS, in 1993, he moved to Washington, D.C., reprising his role as Chief of Staff for
18 United States Representative Nathan Deal, serving Georgia's northernmost counties until
19 1995; and
20 WHEREAS, from 1995 to 2011, he served as an executive with the Medical Association of
21 Georgia; and
22 WHEREAS, from 2011 to 2013, he served as the Commissioner of the Georgia Department
23 of Community Health; and
24 WHEREAS, in 2013, he was selected to serve as the 43rd Secretary of the Georgia State
25 Senate, and he has since upgraded the Senate's electronic voting system, procured the current
26 Senate voting board, and helped launch the project to update the General Assembly's
27 Legislative Management System, all while maintaining the operations and good order of the
28 Office of the Secretary; and
29 WHEREAS, he succeeded in accomplishing this for the past 11 years and has left in place
30 a staff who will ensure that the work of the Office of the Secretary continues at the high
31 standard the Senate has come to expect.
32 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
33 recognize and commend Mr. David A. Cook for his efficient, effective, unselfish, and
34 dedicated service to the Georgia State Senate and the State of Georgia; congratulate him
